# Performance testing SOP

Target: physical GPU 0, Blackwell CC 12.0.

## Entrypoints

```bash
./perf.sh quick <op>
./perf.sh quick <op> --baseline <name>
./perf.sh full <op> --baseline <name>
./perf.sh baseline create <name> <op> --from <run-id>
./perf.sh baseline update <name> <op> --from <run-id>
./perf.sh baseline show <name> <op>
```

Quick is the source of truth for CUDA Event latency and regression status. Full runs the fixed case matrix and profiles only the configured representative case.

## Operator definitions

- Quick cases: `<small>`, `<large>`
- Full cases: `<fixed tier list>`
- Representative case: `<case>`
- Variants/reference: `<variants>`
- Algorithm FLOPs: `<formula>`
- Algorithm minimum bytes: `<formula>`
- Peak compute/bandwidth source: `<source>`

## Gates

- Correctness must pass before timing.
- Regression requires both `>5%` relative and `>0.2 us` absolute slowdown, confirmed twice.
- Missing baselines are reported and never auto-created.
- Active compute processes, failed GPU-state queries or temperature `>=85 C` produce `UNSTABLE`.
- Profiler failures produce `PROFILE_PARTIAL` while retaining benchmark results.

## Privilege policy

Authenticate once with `sudo -v`; use privilege only for NCU and ownership repair; keep the ticket alive during Full; clear it with `sudo -k`. Never store or pipe a password.

## Artifacts

Track JSON/Markdown reports and named baselines. Ignore raw Nsight reports, profiler SQLite files and build outputs. Record reproduction commands and environment/source identity in every run.
